          What drives property values in Graceville?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Graceville property values vary by block size, position and condition. The suburb sits at a meaningful discount to Chelmer while sharing similar character stock and school catchments, which draws buyers who want the inner south-west lifestyle at a more accessible price point.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Graceville?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Graceville homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb draws buyers from a wide inner south-west catchment who are comparing Graceville against Chelmer, Sherwood and Corinda simultaneously, which keeps the active buyer pool broad.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Graceville?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Graceville has a quiet, family-orientated lifestyle anchored by Graceville State School, easy rail access on the Ipswich Line, and the Oxley Creek corridor. The suburb sits between Chelmer and Sherwood, giving residents access to both riverside amenity and the convenience of Sherwood Road retail.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Graceville a good suburb to buy in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Graceville offers strong fundamentals: good school catchments, a direct rail connection to the CBD, character housing stock on generous blocks, and a consistent family buyer pool. Buyers who find Chelmer beyond reach frequently target Graceville as the natural next choice on the inner south-west corridor.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

